---

## 9.2 Structural (unsupervised)

### Stability (MOST IMPORTANT)
- consistency under noise / resampling

### Persistence across scale
- clusters survive parameter changes

### Density coherence
- local support within clusters

### Separation
- inter vs intra cluster distance

### Parsimony
- avoid over-fragmentation

---

## 9.3 Task-based (most important in practice)

### Retrieval
- Recall@k
- Precision@k

### Downstream performance
- classification
- anomaly detection

